{"id": "EUVD-2025-22652", "enisaUuid": "49b8f465-8fe9-3b59-a48e-9b0de8a5a003", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nsmb: client: fix regression with native SMB symlinks\n\nSome users and customers reported that their backup/copy tools started\nto fail when the directory being copied contained symlink targets that\nthe client couldn't parse - even when those symlinks weren't followed.\n\nFix this by allowing lstat(2) and readlink(2) to succeed even when the\nclient can't resolve the symlink target, restoring old behavior.", "datePublished": "2025-07-25T15:30:54", "dateUpdated": "2025-11-19T21:31:17", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/6ddaf7567080c7de2e0c99efca2ee1e6b79beea5", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/ff8abbd248c1f52df0c321690b88454b13ff54b2", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2025-38431"], "aliases": ["CVE-2025-38431"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.02, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "03c892ff-4754-3053-8596-9b7388a27b74", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "12b466eb52d926802b6898d2cb7e67386467f54a <ff8abbd248c1f52df0c321690b88454b13ff54b2"}, {"id": "233ce048-4093-33c8-9b74-4af81953404f", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.16"}, {"id": "27f191be-6994-3072-b499-17387bbf2055", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.15.5"}, {"id": "41180e76-26b1-3cc2-ad82-cc72fd48dde6", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "64eec712-b73d-3cf8-8ed2-d5c093cc2652", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.16-rc4"}, {"id": "bf62cc2a-8b27-3bfc-b323-8f7f641be35e", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "12b466eb52d926802b6898d2cb7e67386467f54a <6ddaf7567080c7de2e0c99efca2ee1e6b79beea5"}, {"id": "f2401092-343d-33a4-b14c-65edf0b9c9ef", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "6.14"}], "enisaIdVendor": [{"id": "e4e7df2c-4dbb-3810-b1a1-11c3180f29e0", "vendor": {"name": "Linux"}}], "i